comment: * WebViewRenderProcess provides an opaque handle to a {@link WebView} renderer.

methods.name: public abstract boolean terminate()
methods.comment:
* Cause this renderer to terminate. * *

Calling this on a not yet started, or an already terminated renderer will have no effect. * *

Terminating a renderer process may have an effect on multiple {@link WebView} instances. * *

Renderer termination must be handled by properly overriding * {@link WebViewClient#onRenderProcessGone} for every WebView that shares this * renderer. If termination is not handled by all associated WebViews, then the application * process will also be terminated. * * @return {@code true} if it was possible to terminate this renderer, {@code false} otherwise.
